f(x)= \ln \frac1{1-x}
\sum_{k=0}^\infty x^k
f(x) = \ln\frac{1}{1-x} = - \ln(1-x)
f'(x) = \frac{1}{1-x}
\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} z^k = \frac{1}{1-z}
0\leq|z| \leq x < 1
\ln \frac1{1-x}=-\ln(1-x) = \int_{0}^{x}\frac{dz}{1-z}=\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \int_{0}^{x}z^kdz =\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{x^{k+1}}{k+1} = \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \frac{x^{k}}{k}.
-1 < x \leq 0.
-\ln(1-x)
